sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Creation Suspicious File In Uncommon AppData Folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of suspicious files and folders inside the user's AppData folder but not inside any of the common and well known directories (Local, Romaing, LocalLow). This method could be used as a method to bypass detection who exclude the AppData folder in fear of FPs
Adversaries may abuse Visual Basic (VB) for execution
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Creation of an Executable by an Executable
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an executable by another executable

mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: Stores files to the Windows startup directory
Creates a process in suspended mode (likely to inject code)
Creates files inside the user directory
May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis
Creates files in the recycle bin to hide itself
Monitors certain registry keys / values for changes (often done to protect autostart functionality)
Checks the free space of harddrives
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device
Uses HTTPS for network communication, use the SSL MITM Proxy cookbook for further analysis
